# STEP-BY-STEP EXPLANATION
    zero_rows, zero_cols = set(), set()
Two empty sets, zero_rows and zero_cols, are created to store the indices of the rows and columns with a zero value.

    for i in range(len(matrix)):
        for j in range(len(matrix[0])):
            if matrix[i][j] == 0:
                zero_rows.add(i)
                zero_cols.add(j)

Loops through the entire matrix and checks each element to see if it is zero. If it is, the index of the row and column are added to their respective sets, zero_rows and zero_cols.

    for i in zero_rows:
        matrix[i] = [0] * len(matrix[0])

Next loop goes through each index in zero_rows and sets the entire row to zero by creating a new list of zeros with the same length as the row and assigning it to the row.

    for j in zero_cols:
        for i in range(len(matrix)):
            matrix[i][j] = 0

Last loop goes through each index in zero_cols and sets the entire column to zero by looping through each row and setting the value at that column index to zero.

That's it!

