**Approach 1 (using extra space)**

This Approach will use two boolean 1 dimensional matrices, named rowZero and colZero.
- rowZero[i] and colZero[j] will indicate if matrix[i][j] == 0. That is, for each column and row we are storing if it contains a 0 or not in the first traversal. If it contains a 0, mark it as true.
- In the second traversal, for each matrix[i][j], if rowZero[i] is true OR colZero[j] is true, then we place a 0 at matrix[i][j]. 
- Else keep matrix[i][j] as it is.
- Time Complexity: 2 * O(M*N)
- Space Complexity: O(M) + O(N)
```
void setZeroes(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        int rowSize = matrix.size(), colSize = matrix[0].size();
        vector<bool> rowZero(rowSize);
        vector<bool> colZero(colSize);

        for(int i=0;i<rowSize;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<colSize;j++){
                if(matrix[i][j] == 0) {
                    rowZero[i] = true;
                    colZero[j] = true;
                }
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<rowSize;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<colSize;j++){
                if(rowZero[i] == true || colZero[j] == true) matrix[i][j] = 0;
            }
        }        
    }
```
**Approach 2 (O(1) SPACE)**
We will use two bool variables rowZero and colZero to store whether first row or col has a 0 or not. Then we use first row and first col itself to store whether the remaining rows/cols has zero or not. That is, instead of creating two separate arrays like in first approach, we will instead use the first row and first column of the given matrix itself. This will reduce space complexity to constant space **O(1)**. 
**Time Complexity will remain O(M*N)**
```
void setZeroes(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {

        bool rowZero = false, colZero = false;
        int rowSize = matrix.size(), colSize = matrix[0].size();

        // check for first col
        for(int i=0;i<rowSize;i++){
            if(matrix[i][0] == 0){
                colZero = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        // check for first row 
        for(int j=0;j<colSize;j++){
            if(matrix[0][j] == 0){
                rowZero = true;
                break;
            }
        }
        // mark 0 in first row/col where the remaining part of matrix has zero or not.
        for(int i=1;i<rowSize;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<colSize;j++){
                if(matrix[i][j] == 0){
                    matrix[0][j] = 0;
                    matrix[i][0] = 0;
                }
            }
        }
        // setting the matrix as 0 wherever required except the first row or col
        for(int i=1;i<rowSize;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<colSize;j++){
                if(matrix[0][j] == 0|| matrix[i][0] == 0) matrix[i][j] = 0;
            }
        }

        if(rowZero){
            for(int j=0;j<colSize;j++) matrix[0][j] = 0;
        }
        if(colZero){
            for(int i=0;i<rowSize;i++) matrix[i][0] = 0;
        }

    }
