1.BRUTE FORCE APPROACH
LINEARLY TRAVERSING CHECKING IF THERE IS A ZERO IF YES THEN MARKING WHOLE ROW AND COL ZERO
```
class solution {
      public void setZeroes(int[][] arr) {
            int n = arr.length;
            int m = arr[0].length;
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                  for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                        if (arr[i][j] == 0) {
                              //FOR MARKING WHOLE ROW 0 OR Integer.MIN_VALUE
                              for (int a = 0; a < m; a++) {
                                    if (arr[i][a] != 0) {
                                          arr[i][a] = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
                                    }

                              }
                              //FOR MARKING WHOLE COLUMN 0 OR Integer.MIN_VALUE
                              for (int a = 0; a < n; a++) {
                                    if (arr[a][j] != 0) {
                                          arr[a][j] = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
                                    }
                              }
                        }
                  }
            }
            //THEN AT LAST MARKING ZERO AT PLACES OF Integer.MIN_VALUE
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                  for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                        if (arr[i][j] == Integer.MIN_VALUE) {
                              arr[i][j] = 0;
                        }
                  }
            }
      }
}
```
2.BETTER APPROACH
BY TAKING TWO DUMMY ARRAYS.
```
class solution {
      public void setZeroes(int[][] arr) {
          int n = arr.length;
          int m = arr[0].length;
          //making two dummy array
          int row[] = new int[n];
          int col[] = new int[m];
          for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
          {
              for(int j=0;j<m;j++)
              {
                  if(arr[i][j]==0)
                  {
                     row[i]=-1;
                     col[j]=-1;
                  }
              }   
          }
          //upto this point we filled our dummy array with zero.
          //i.e. 2 1D dummay array bnae then traverse kra given array ko ,, then as soon as we encounter 0 then we will mark 0 at i index of dummay array row and mark 0 at jth index of dummay array col->> after traversing the whole array we will know if there is a zero in given row or col or not.

          //again traverse through given array and with help of 1D dummy arrays check for the particular index that if in any one of row or col arrays there is a zero marked if yes then mark that particular index zero in the given array and so on.
           for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
           {
              for(int j=0;j<m;j++)
              {
                  if(row[i]==-1 || col[j]==-1)
                  {
                      arr[i][j]=0;
                  }
              }
           }
      }
  }
  ```
 3.OPTIMAL APPROACH 
THIS APPROACH IS SAME AS BETTER APPROACH BUT INSTEAD OF TAKING TWO DUMMY ARRAYS WE USE FIRST ROW AND COL OF GIVEN MATRIX FOR CALCULATING ANSWER.
```
  class Solution {
      public void setZeroes(int[][] arr) {
          int n = arr.length;
          int m = arr[0].length;

          int colo=1;
          //THIS VARIABLE IS FOR ENSURING THAT WE WILL NOT MARK A WHOLE ROW OR COL ZERO BCZ OF PRESENCE OF A ZERO IN DUMMY PART OF ARRAY AS IT WILL RUIN OUR ANSWER SO WE ARE ASSUMING THAT WE HAVE CHECKED FOR FIRST ROW AND COL AND THEN STARTED TRAVERSING FROM  INDEX (1,1).
          for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
          {
              if(arr[i][0]==0)
              {
                  colo=0;
              }
              for(int j=1;j<m;j++)
              {
                  if(arr[i][j]==0)
                  {
                      //IF FOUND ZERO THEN MARKING 0 IN THE UPPERMOST AND LEFTMOST PART ZERO i.e. MARKING 0 IN DUMMY ARRAY WHICH IS PRESENT IN OUR GIVEN ARRAY.
                      arr[i][0]=arr[0][j]=0; 
                  }
              }   
          }

          //STARTING FROM BACK AS WE WOULD NOT THEN WE WILL UPDATE OUR DUMMY ARRAY FIRST WHICH WHICH RUIN OUR ANSWER
          //EVERYTHING ELSE IS SAME LIKE BETTER APPROACH.
          //ONLY COLO IS THERE WHICH ENSURES THAT WE WILL NOT MARK OUR A WHOLE ROW ZERO BCZ OF PRESENCE OF A ZERO IN OUR DUMMY ARRAY.
          for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--)
          {
            //TRAVESING FROM BACK
              for(int j=m-1;j>=1;j--)
              {
                  if(arr[i][0]==0 || arr[0][j]==0)
                  {
                      arr[i][j]=0;
                  }
              }
              //IF WE FOUNF ZERO IN OU FIRST COL THEN WE WILL WHOLE COL ZERO.
              if(colo==0)
              {
                  arr[i][0]=0;
              }
          }
      }
  }
  ```
