1. `BSTIterator(root)`
    - ` back ->` [ 7, 3 ] `<- top`
2. `next()` 
    - `back ->` [ 7 ] `<- top` `pop 3`, `return 3` then push all the element of `right of left` trees,
3. `next() `
    - `back ->` [ ] `<- top` `pop 7` & `return 7`
    - become `back ->` [ 15, 9 ] `<- top` `pop 7`
4. `hasNext()` return next element present or not i.e `is stack empty`
