# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Tried to use Threaded Binary Tree concept
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
First we check if the tree has any left child if it has we connect the right most node of the left child to the parent. and move to the left of the tree. 
If the there is no left child then according to the inorder traversal we return the value of the root and root is changed to root->right;
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->O(1) on an average for each operation.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->O(1) as no extra space is used

# Code
class BSTIterator {
private : 
TreeNode * root;
public:

    BSTIterator(TreeNode* r) {
        root = r;
    }

    int next() {
        while (root->left)
        {
            TreeNode *tmp = root->left;
            while(tmp->right && tmp->right != root) tmp = tmp->right;
            if (tmp->right == NULL)
            {
                tmp->right = root;
                root = root->left;
            }
            else
            {
                tmp->right = NULL;
                int ans = root->val;
                root = root->right;
                return ans;
            }

        }
        int ans = root->val;
        root = root->right;
        return ans;
    }

    bool hasNext() {
        return root != NULL;
    }
};

