We create a ArrayList (tree) to store the value of nodes of the tree, in inorder sequence.
When the BSTIterator is called for the first time, we call normal inorder function that traverses the tree, and we strore the node values in the tree.

We also create a pointer l = 0, that traverses the Arraylist, and keeps track of the posititon in the tree.
