# Approach
This solution is similar to the previous one, but it defines the word lists and scales as instance variables of the class instead of local variables inside the function. It also defines a separate convert function to handle converting each group of three digits, and uses recursion to break down numbers greater than 100 into smaller parts. Finally, it removes any trailing spaces from the resulting string using the strip() method.

