solutions.content:
Need to proces the digits in groups of 3 since that's how the patterns repeat. Each new group of 3 digits can get the "thousands" designation representing a number larger than zero.  Notice that "Ten" is in the teens group since it's a special case of when digit2 is a 1 this way I didn't need to create any special handling for it.

I'm using a stack for easy reversal of the string output at the end. 
Don't forget about the Zero :)

```
class Solution {

    private String[] ones = new String[] {
        "", "One", "Two", "Three", "Four", "Five", "Six", "Seven", "Eight", "Nine"
    };

    private String[] teens = new String[] {
        "Ten", "Eleven", "Twelve", "Thirteen", "Fourteen", "Fifteen", "Sixteen", "Seventeen", "Eighteen", "Nineteen"
    };

    private String[] tens = new String[] {
        "", "", "Twenty", "Thirty", "Forty", "Fifty", "Sixty", "Seventy", "Eighty", "Ninety"
    };

    private String[] thousands = new String[] {
        "", "Thousand", "Million", "Billion"
    };

    public String numberToWords(int num) {

        if(num == 0) return "Zero";

        Deque<String> stack = new ArrayDeque<String>();
        int group = 0;

        // Process the digits in groups of 3

        while(num > 0) {
            int digit3 = num % 10; num /= 10;
            int digit2 = num % 10; num /= 10;
            int digit1 = num % 10; num /= 10;

            if(digit1 * 100 + digit2 * 10 + digit3 > 0) {
                stack.push(thousands[group]);
            }

            if(digit2 == 1) {
                stack.push(teens[digit3]);
            } else {
                stack.push(ones[digit3]);
                stack.push(tens[digit2]);
            }
            if(digit1 > 0) {
                stack.push("Hundred");
                stack.push(ones[digit1]);                
            }

            group++;
        }

        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        while(stack.size() > 0) {
            String s = stack.pop();
            if(s.length() > 0) {
                if(sb.length() > 0) sb.append(" ");
                sb.append(s);
            }
        }

        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```

