**ANSWER :** 
We know that we need only k values. We will map each index of nums1 to nums2 and we need to find the first k smallest sum pairs....so we can find the first k ans while mapping it. In this way it will be faster.
How will we do that? 
let us first map each i with 0 and push it in the min heap according to its sum ----> pq.push(nums[i]+nums[0]) . Now we have minmium sum pair at the top.
Now we can iterate k-times and then take out the top sum and then increase the mapped index of i e.g earlier it was (i,0) now it will be (i,1) and then update its sum and push it in the heap. 
There will be one validation that if we have (i, j) and if we increase j++ then we check if j<num2.size() or not if yes then only we can push it in the queue else we will not push it.


